  amd64/x86 stable, bug #250348

  14 Dec 2008; nixnut <nixnut@gentoo.org> rspec-1.1.11.ebuild:
  Stable on ppc wrt bug 250348

  12 Dec 2008; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> -rspec-1.0.8.ebuild,
  -rspec-1.1.3.ebuild, -rspec-1.1.8.ebuild, -rspec-1.1.9.ebuild,
  -rspec-1.1.10.ebuild:
  Remove old versions

  10 Dec 2008; Ferris McCormick <fmccor@gentoo.org> rspec-1.1.11.ebuild:
  Add ~sparc keyword, part of Bug #250348.

  09 Dec 2008; Brent Baude <ranger@gentoo.org> rspec-1.1.11.ebuild:
  Marking rspec-1.1.11 ~ppc64 for bug 250348

  25 Oct 2008; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> rspec-1.1.11.ebuild:
  Add back hoe dependency because it is still listed as a runtime dependency

*rspec-1.1.11 (25 Oct 2008)

  25 Oct 2008; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> +rspec-1.1.11.ebuild:
  Version bump that no longer requires development-only dependencies

*rspec-1.1.10 (24 Oct 2008)

  24 Oct 2008; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> +rspec-1.1.10.ebuild:
  Version bump with one minor enhancement and two minor bugfixes.

*rspec-1.1.9 (21 Oct 2008)

  21 Oct 2008; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> +rspec-1.1.9.ebuild:
  Version bump. Deprecated functionality has been removed and a number of bugs
  have been fixed. Drop hoe dependency since it is only needed for development
  of rspec itself and rubygems can now express this.

  04 Oct 2008; Markus Meier <maekke@gentoo.org> rspec-1.1.4.ebuild:
  x86 stable, bug #239505

  04 Oct 2008; Brent Baude <ranger@gentoo.org> rspec-1.1.4.ebuild:
  stable ppc, bug 239505

  04 Oct 2008; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> rspec-1.1.4.ebuild:
  Mark stable for amd64

*rspec-1.1.8 (04 Oct 2008)

  04 Oct 2008; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> -rspec-1.1.5.ebuild,
  -rspec-1.1.7.ebuild, +rspec-1.1.8.ebuild:
  Version bump with fixes for the bugs in 1.1.7 that I reported upstream.
  Removing two previous versions since both have problems.

